      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MCROCKIN (3) has been in the placings two times from as many runs this prep. Recorded yet another strong performance last start when she battled on bravely to just miss out over 1780m at this track, adding to a string of recent minor placings. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Primary contender based on what we have seen of late. WICKED VICTREE (1) finished fifth last start, beaten 9 metres at this track over 1780m. Capable of playing a major role so has to be respected. ARKANSAURUS (2) is a likely improver after debuting with a solid third last time out over 1780m at this track. GIRL SECRETS (9) broke after being checked and finished tailed off on debut last start over 1850m at Marburg. Hard to know where she gets from this slightly awkward draw. This doesn't look as hard so she is capable of turning things around.",
